'''迈克尔·D·勒莫尼克'''（{{lang-en|Michael D. Lemonick}}，{{bd|1953年|10月13日|}}）是一位[[美国|美国]]科学记者和[[科学普及|科普]]作家<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=aZISUZ6gLV4|title=Is It Time to Give Up on Dark Matter?|accessdate=12 August 2019|archive-date=2019-05-07|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190507050639/https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=aZISUZ6gLV4&gl=US&hl=en|dead-url=no}}</ref>，是《[[科学美国人|科学美国人]]》杂志的意见编辑，也为《[[发现_(杂志)|发现]]》等杂志撰稿<ref>[http://climatecentral.org/about/people-bio/michael_lemonick Bio] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20100210002540/http://www.climatecentral.org/about/people-bio/michael_lemonick |date=2010-02-10 }} climatecentral.org</ref><ref>Lemonick has written more than 50 cover stories on topics for ''Time'' magazine, including the topics of [http://www.time.com/time/magazine/article/0,9171,999630,00.html climate change] {{Wayback|url=http://www.time.com/time/magazine/article/0,9171,999630,00.html |date=20090826163021 }}, [http://www.time.com/time/magazine/article/0,9171,1376229,00.html astronomy] {{Wayback|url=http://www.time.com/time/magazine/article/0,9171,1376229,00.html |date=20100513153804 }}, [http://www.time.com/time/magazine/article/0,9171,1640436,00.html addiction] {{Wayback|url=http://www.time.com/time/magazine/article/0,9171,1640436,00.html |date=20100902001053 }}, and [http://www.time.com/time/magazine/article/0,9171,991790,00.html human origins] {{Wayback|url=http://www.time.com/time/magazine/article/0,9171,991790,00.html |date=20090902075645 }}.</ref><ref>{{Cite web |url=http://discovermagazine.com/2009/mar/06-world.s-hardest-working-telescope/?searchterm=lemonick%20sdss |title=The World's Hardest working Telescope |access-date=2020-11-18 |archive-date=2012-10-06 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20121006072344/http://discovermagazine.com/2009/mar/06-world.s-hardest-working-telescope/?searchterm=lemonick%20sdss |dead-url=no }}</ref>，作品有《发现天王星——开创现代天文学的[[威廉·赫歇爾|赫歇尔]][[卡羅琳·赫歇爾|兄妹]]》（''The Georgian Star: How William and Caroline Herschel Revolutionized Our Understanding of the Cosmos''）等<ref>[https://www.amazon.com/dp/039306574X The ''Georgian'' Star]</ref><ref>{{cite journal|author=Kissack, Randy S.|title=Book Review: ''The Georgian Star: How William and Caroline Herschel revolutionized our understanding of the cosmos'', by Michael D. Lemonick.|journal=Meteoritics & Planetary Science Archives|volume=44|issue=5|year=2009|pages=781–782|url=https://journals.uair.arizona.edu/index.php/maps/article/view/15734|access-date=2020-11-18|archive-date=2020-09-01|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200901184256/https://journals.uair.arizona.edu/index.php/maps/article/view/15734|dead-url=no}}</ref>。
